Democracy and sustainability
Doubts about the feasibility of democratic solutions to the sustainability crisis have commonly been fended 
AND
that is geared more towards stabilizing than radically changing the unsustainable status quo.
Doubts about the capacity of democracy to deal with environmental problems are, of course
AND
